Q: A car is being driven, in a straight line and at a uniform speed, towards the base of a vertical tower. The top of the tower is observed from the car and, in the process, it takes 10 minutes for the angle of elevation to change from 45° to 60°. After how much more time will this car reach the base of the tower?
Answer Choices: (A) 5 (√3 + 1)  (B) 6 (√3 + √2)  (C) 7 (√3 – 1)  (D) 8 (√3 – 2)  (E) None of these
label: A
reasoning_chains:
A: The car is driving in a straight line, so the distance it has to travel is the same as the height of the tower. The angle of elevation changes from 45° to 60°, so the change in height is 60° - 45° = 15°. Since the angle of elevation is changing at a uniform rate, the time it takes for the angle of elevation to change by 1° is 10 minutes. So the time it takes for the angle of elevation to change by 15° is 15 * 10 minutes = 150 minutes. Therefore, it will take 150 minutes more for the car to reach the base of the tower. 

So the answer is (E).
